The use of the fields \texttt{permID}, \texttt{provID}, \texttt{trkID}, \texttt{trkSub}, and \texttt{obsID} depends on the designation status of the target and the purpose behind the exchange of data. For all observer submissions to the MPC, at least one of \texttt{permID}, \texttt{provID} or \texttt{trkSub} must be filled. For unlinked submissions to the MPC the \texttt{permID} and \texttt{provID} fields should not be filled and \texttt{trkSub} must include a user-assigned temporary designation, unique within the submission, for each tracklet in the submission. For targeted follow-up or recovery observations the user is encouraged to report the current designation of the target in either the \texttt{permID} or \texttt{provID} field, as the case may be. If an object is numbered then provID should not be filled and will be ignored by the MPC. For targeted follow up with more than one tracklet in the submission, the \texttt{trkSub} field should be used to distinguish the individual tracklets. \texttt{trkID} and \texttt{obsID} are only to be filled by the MPC and must be empty for MPC submissions of new data. Observers may submit corrections to published observations, in which case the \texttt{obsID} published by the MPC must be included. The following table indicates the correct approach for these fields. \begin{tabularx}{\linewidth}{|X|X|X|X|X|X|} \hline \footnotesize Type of observation & \texttt{permID} & \texttt{provID} & \texttt{trkID} & \texttt{trkSub} & \texttt{obsID} \\ \hline \footnotesize Submission of targeted follow-up observations & \scriptsize Permanent designamtion of target, if applicable & \scriptsize Provisional designation of target if applicable. Ignored by MPC for numbered objects. Could be an NEOCP temporary designation. & \scriptsize Empty & \scriptsize When submission includes multiple tracklets of a targeted object then each tracklet should be identified by a locally unique code & \scriptsize Empty \\ \hline \footnotesize Submission of routine and unlinked survey detections & \scriptsize Empty & \scriptsize Empty & \scriptsize Empty & \scriptsize Observer-assigned identifier for each tracklet in submission. & \scriptsize Empty \\ \hline \footnotesize MPC distribution & \scriptsize Permanent designation of target if applicable. (filled or vetted by MPC) & \scriptsize Provisional designation of target for observations submitted prior to numbering (filled or vetted by MPC) & \scriptsize Filled by MPC with globally unique value & \scriptsize As in observer submission & \scriptsize Filled by MPC with globally unique value \\ \hline \footnotesize Submission of correction to already published observation & \scriptsize As published & \scriptsize As published & \scriptsize As published & \scriptsize As published (unless part of correction) & \scriptsize As published \\ \hline \end{tabularx}
The \texttt{permID} and \texttt{provID} fields carry the permanent or provisional designation of the object, respectively. (The past use of an MPC ``packed" designation has been dropped, primarily because it is generally less readable, and the sorting advantages of the packed format require preservation of leading blanks and zeros, which is not in accord with the IAU2015 formatting guidelines.) For minor planets and comets, the \texttt{permID} and \texttt{provID} format follows the formal designation very closely, with the exception of removing parentheses around numbered minor planets and eschewing subscripting in provisional designations of minor planets. For comets, the formal \texttt{permID} and provID entries are identical, including the fragment descriptor. For planetary satellites the \texttt{permID} entry uses only the first letter of the planet followed by the Arabic number of the satellite. The specification of the permanent and provisional designation fields is given by examples in the following table:
